  "name": "Drug Induced Liver Injury",
  "description": "This test case evaluates the identification of drug-induced liver injury (DILI) patients based on the complex phenotype algorithm. It requires finding patients with liver injury diagnoses, recent medication exposure, and specific laboratory thresholds (ALT \u22655x ULN or ALP \u22652x ULN or ALT \u22653x ULN with Bilirubin \u22652x ULN), while excluding patients with alternative causes of liver injury. This is a multi-step algorithm requiring temporal relationships between drug exposure and abnormal lab values.",
  "prompt": "Find patients with drug-induced liver injury who have elevated liver enzymes (ALT at least 5 times upper normal or alkaline phosphatase at least 2 times upper normal) following medication exposure within the past 3 months.",
